rComments: Class was really interesting if you like that theatre style of class. There was a lot of plays that he makes you read and watch but they are usually pretty interesting ones. A lot of group projects to do where he mostly picked the groups depending on which LAB session you are in.
Super passionate professor, loved taking his course. I've never enjoyed a class as much as this one.

His lecture style is pretty laidback and casual and he presents a lot of facts/history. The problem is that assignments and tests do not reflect how he chooses to teach. He doesnt tell people that they need to use abstract thinking to apply concrete concepts without providing examples. He assigns a LOT of plays to watch & read. NOT A BIRD COURSE!
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Lots of homework', 'Participation matters']

rComments: One of the best profs out there. Great guy.

No exams, just quizzes, a short paper and group scenes. Lectures were funny and engaging but you won't learn much if this isn't your first theatre class. A bit too much casual discussion, things got to a point where people were saying nonsense and shouting over each other. The TAs were good, especially Patrice!
He's the best prof I've ever had. Very passionate and easy going. Not a tough grader. The class is fun!

He is an amazing professor. He is passionate about what he teaches and all of the students love him. I loved the labs and the group activities were really fun. Just be prepared to attend every class and participate.
